               <p>1176. <persName id="def1-1176-18480403" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1176-18480403" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1176-18480403" type="surname" value="MAINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1176-18480403" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES MAINE</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18480403-1176-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18480403-1176-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18480403-1176-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>, stealing 20 pieces of iron piping, and 60lbs. weight of iron, value 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of the <persName id="t18480403-name-1211" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1211" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18480403-1176-offence-1 t18480403-name-1211"></join>London, Brighton, and South Coast Railway Company</persName>; his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. CLARKSON</hi> and <hi rend="smallCaps">PAYNE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-1212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1212" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1212" type="given" value="HUGH"></interp>HUGH STEVENS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a marine store dealer, at Bell-lane, Deptford. The prisoner brought some iron to my shop; some of it was broken piping—I gave him 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for it—there was a quarter of a hundred weight—I kept it till next day, separate from other iron, and gave it to the officer—I had bought</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184804030171"></xptr>
               <p>things of him before—I knew he was in the Company's employ—he said he picked it up coming along.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You were here yesterday? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; in Loder's case—I got some iron from him—I gave its worth for it—he was convicted—I had to give up more than six hundred weight—it was bought honestly—I know I bought this of the prisoner, as it was the day before I was locked up—there is no mark by which I know it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-1213" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1213" type="surname" value="ACTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1213" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ACTON.</persName>
                  </hi> I am superintendent of the London, Brighton, and South Coast Railway Company's police. Charles Pascoe Grenfell is the chairman—the prisoner was a plate-layer in their employ, at the West Station, Croydon—I took him, and said it was a charge of stealing the Company's property; that some iron pipe had been found at Steven's house, which he said he had bought of him the evening before—he said he was very sorry; he did not think he doing any harm; he picked it up on the line—it is worth 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—it was worth 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. or 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. before it was broken up—the Company do not sell their pipe, or break it up—the prisoner had no right to break it up, or to sell things found on the line.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q</hi> Did not he say he found it in the <hi rend="italic">lane</hi>? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; on the line—I found about 18cwt. of stolen iron at Stevens's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-1214" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1214" type="surname" value="BONNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1214" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES BONNER.</persName>
                  </hi> I am deputy superintendent of the locomotive depart<lb></lb>ment. This piece of iron pipe belongs to the Company—the believe it was recently broken when I first saw it—we do not break up iron or sell it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What is done with pipe accidentally broken? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It is put on one side, and I suppose would be sold, but we never had a sale before yesterday.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480403-name-1215" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1215" type="surname" value="BUCKMASTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480403-name-1215" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH BUCKMASTER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, R</hi> 39.) On 22nd Feb. I went to Stevens—he pointed out some iron pipe to me—I took it, and produce a por<lb></lb>tion of it—I was present when Acton spoke to the prisoner about it—he said he was very sorry, he found it on his way home on the line—he said some<lb></lb>thing about a <hi rend="italic">lane</hi> before the Magistrate.</p>
